<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="N" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Nut" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Nut,</orth> the fruit of the tree Corylus: <bibl n="shak. mnd 4.1.40" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. IV, 1, 40</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 3.2.115" default="NO" valid="yes">As III, 2, 115</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 3.2.115" default="NO" valid="yes">As III, 2, 115</bibl> <bibl n="shak. ayl 3.4.27" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 4, 27</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. aww 2.5.48" default="NO" valid="yes">All's II, 5, 48</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 2.1.111" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. II, 1, 111</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 3.1.21" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. III, 1, 21</bibl>. Used to denote a trifle: <cit><quote>a rush, a hair, a drop of blood, a pin, a n., a cherry-stone,</quote> <bibl n="shak. err 4.3.74" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. IV, 3, 74</bibl></cit>.
